'''Gabrielle Christian''' (born '''Gabrielle Christine Horchler'''; July 30, 1984)<ref name=Facts>{{cite web|title=Facts|url=http://www.gabriellechristian.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=71&Itemid=70|publisher=www.gabriellechristian.com|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> is an American actress and singer best known for her portrayal of [[Spencer Carlin]] in [[The N]] original series ''[[South of Nowhere]]'' and her portrayal of [[Colby Robson]] in the web series [[Girltrash!]] and its musical prequel film [[Girltrash!: All Night Long]]. In addition, she has also guest starred on ''[[Drake & Josh]]'', ''[[Windfall (television series)|Windfall]]'', ''[[Without a Trace]]'', and ''[[What Should You Do?]]''.
==Early life and career== Christian was born '''Gabrielle Christian Horchler''' in [[Washington, D.C.]] to parents Gabe and Joani. She grew up in [[Cheverly, Maryland]]. She began performing in plays at age 12. She has four sisters (Gen, Steph, Jules, Ili). Christian acquired her first acting job while she still attending high school at Eleanor Roosevelt High School located in [[Greenbelt, Maryland]], on the television series ''[[Young Americans (TV series)|Young Americans]]''.<ref name=Facts/> She studied one and half years of theater at the [[University of Pittsburgh]], before relocating to [[Los Angeles, California]] after landing roles on several television series.<ref name=Facts/>
==Career== Christian relocated to Los Angeles after landing roles on the [[What Should You Do?]], [[Without a Trace]], [[Drake & Josh]] television series's.<ref name=Film>{{cite web|title=Filmography|url=http://www.gabriellechristian.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=blogcategory&id=34&Itemid=75|publisher=www.gabriellechristian.com|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> Her most notable role was portraying [[Spencer Carlin]] on [[TeenNick|The Nâs]] hit television series [[South of Nowhere]] which aired for three seasons between 2005â2008.<ref name="Facts"/> Outside of South Of Nowhere Christian has appeared on several other television series, she appeared on [[CSI: Miami]] as Amy Hobbs in the Season six episode [[CSI: Miami (season 6)#Episodes|Permanent Vacation]].<ref name=Film/> In 2006 she appeared as Miranda Keyton in the [[Windfall_(TV_series)#Episode_list|Truth Be Told and Priceless]] episodes of [[Windfall]]. In 2007 Christian portrayed Colby Robson in [[Angela Robinson]]'s [[Girltrash!]] web-series along side South of Nowhere co-star Mandy Musgrave. In 2008 she appeared in the [[List of Numb3rs episodes (season 4)#Episodes|Atomic No. 33]] episode of [[Numb3rs]].<ref name=Film/> Also in 2008 she appeared in the web-series ''3Way'' as Cindy Shims, however her episode''Ladycops'', was not posted as a regular episode during the duration of the series. In 2010 she appeared as Justine Grogan the daughter of Abbey Grogan ([[Jennifer Grey]]) on the [[Unplanned Parenthood (House)|Unplanned Parenthood]] episode of [[House (TV series)|House]].<ref>{{cite web|title=GABRIELLE CHRISTIAN TO GUEST STAR ON HOUSE!|url=http://hollywoodteenzine.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1369&Itemid=48|publisher=hollywoodteenzine.com|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> In August 2011 she guest starred on [[The Protector (TV series)|The Protector]] as lab assistant Laurel Nash. Christian has two films yet to be released the first being ''You're Cordially Uninvited'' where she portrays Rose, A woman whom is getting ready to get married to another woman ''Lisa'', but wishes not to have to face her parents and how theyâll react to it. The Second film yet to be released is the Musical prequel to the Girltrash! web-series titled [[Girltrash: All Night Long]] where she will once again portray Colby Robson.<ref name=Film/>
On June 2, 2011 Christian released her first single entitled ''Kissing Mandy'' to [[iTunes]].<ref name=KissingMandy/>
==Personal life== Christian helps her mother with the [[Sudden infant death syndrome]] (SIDS) organization. This organization was created by her mother after the loss of her son in 1991. She uses the surname Christian in memory of her brother. Her mother has written a book, often known as the SIDS "Bible". The book features a poem Christian wrote when she was 8.<ref name=Facts/>
Christian became the spokesperson for the organization FAIR Fund,<ref name="FAIR FUND">{{cite web|title=ABOUT FAIR FUND|url=http://www.fairfund.org/subpage.asp?P=about&S=default|publisher=www.fairfund.org|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> which works to engage youth in the areas of anti-trafficking, domestic violence, and sexual assault prevention. She hosts cocktail events to showcase jewelry made by girls participating in the JewelGirls program.<ref name=jewelGirlz>{{cite web|title=JewelGirls|url=http://www.fairfund.org/subpage.asp?P=about&S=programs&T=jewelGirlz|publisher=www.fairfund.org|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref> Christian's father is from Hungary. She speaks fluent Hungarian, conversational French, and basic Russian.<ref name="AE">{{Cite news|last = Nai|first = Dara|coauthors=|title=Interview with Gabrielle Christian| newspaper= | location=| pages=| language= | publisher= [[AfterEllen]]| date=2008-11-30| url=http://www.afterellen.com/people/2008/12/gabriellechristian?page=0,3| accessdate=2009-11-18}}</ref>
Christian maintains close friendships with follow South of Nowhere cast members [[Maeve Quinlan]] and [[Mandy Musgrave]]. Christian married long time boyfriend Justin Mentzer on July 11, 2009 at Saint Timothy's Chapel in Mentzer's home town of [[Drummond, Montana]] with the reception held at the Mentzer's family ranch.<ref name=TIESTHEKNOT>{{cite web|title=SOUTH OF NOWHERE STAR GABRIELLE CHRISTIAN TIES THE KNOT!|url=http://hollywoodteenzine.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=470&Itemid=48|publisher=www.hollywoodteenzine.com|accessdate=22 April 2011}}</ref>
